6 132ND LEGISLATURE
7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 383, L.D. 894, “An Act to Amend the Laws
9 Governing Paid Family and Medical Leave”
10 Amend the bill by inserting after the enacting clause and before section 1 the following:
11 'Sec. 1. 26 MRSA §850-A, sub-§9, as enacted by PL 2023, c. 412, Pt. AAA, §7, is
12 amended to read:
13 9. Covered individual. "Covered individual" means a person who:
14 A. Earned at least 6 times the state average weekly wage in wages subject to premiums
15 under this subchapter during the individual's base period or elects coverage and meets
16 the requirements of section 850‑G; and
17 B. Meets the administrative requirements outlined in this subchapter and any rules
18 adopted pursuant to this subchapter and files an application for family leave benefits
19 or medical leave benefits.; and
20 C. Has been employed for at least 120 days by the employer from whom the employee
21 is taking leave.'
22 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
23 number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment requires an employee to be employed with an employer for a
2266 minimum of 120 days before being eligible for paid leave.
